newsitem.title: UK: NWE gasoline up, support seen from the U.S.
newsitem.headline: NWE gasoline up, support seen from the U.S.

text.p: NWE oil products were mixed on Monday.
Gasoline edged up $1 but activity was slow. Some dealers still expect support from the United States to emerge over the next couple of days.
Naphtha was little changed despite modest crude and gasoline gains.
Gas oil added $2-$4 a tonne as healthy German demand lifted spot market premiums, magnifying a rally on benchmark futures.

High sulphur barges steadied after trading higher at $85 fob ARA, but thin demand brought the levels down to as low as $83.25, within Friday's early range. Low sulphur barges were quietly talked flat at $95/$97.
High sulphur cargoes were talked firm, after two cracked Russian cargoes changed hands late on Friday at $82 cif, a little higher than trades early last week.
One percent was heard offered a little higher at $95 but buyers were $2 below that level.
